SIMPLE: nonage
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nonage
<hw>Non"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>nonagium</ets>, from L. <ets>nonus</ets> ninth, <ets>novem</ets>
nine.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The ninth part of movable goods,
formerly payable to the clergy on the death of persons in their
parishes.</def> <rj><au>Mozley & W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nonage
<hw>Non"age</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>non-</ets> +
<ets>age</ets>.]</ety> <def>Time of life before a person becomes of age;
legal immaturity; minority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The human mind . . . was still in its <qex>nonage</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonaged</ent>⟦br⟧
